layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 21; written lines: 21; Biblical verses are given in square characters.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Oriental square and semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of 15th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Yefet. Com. on Genesis. Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2461.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 08 July 1882, folio [188v].
